Caption @juliancarr -  Topic of visual acuity: 20/20 vision means something that is 20 feet away, in detail, it looks 20 feet away.  If you have 20/200 vision, it means something that is 20 feet away, in detail, looks 200 feet away. I’m lucky to have 20/10 vision, something that is 20 feet away, in detail, looks 10 feet away. I believe my eyesight has contributed to my passion/ability for bigger airs. When I’m on a take-off, I can look down at the landing, see the landing in detail, make sense of what I’m about to do, reason w it, truly interpret it. Rather than just ‘sacking up’. PC:@willwiss

@ryanintheus - "Jemma and I just had an incredible long weekend at the very beautiful and very family friendly @skibigwhite resort in BC, Canada. Over the weekend we took multiple ski lessons, went ice skating, tubing, rode on a horse drawn sleigh ride, went hot tubbing outside, watched fireworks and even went ice climbing! This is an adventure the two of us will remember forever! On top of all of that the mountain is incredibly beautiful as you can see in this pic. The snow ghosts stand like frozen statues in an all white winter wonderland. We'll be back!" 📷 + caption by @ryanintheus who was visiting from Seattle.

@myswitzerland -  65 metres high, 142 metres long and one of the most photographed structures of the #Rhaetian Railway and perhaps even #Switzerland! But we understand why the #Landwaterviaduct is fascinating not just for train enthusiasts: On a @rhaetischebahn train, riding on the 63-kilometre long #Albula route through @graubuenden… Shortly after the village of #Filisur travelling in the direction of #Chur, the train goes through a tunnel in the vertical wall… then you suddenly get a wonderful view of the elegant bridge. The route makes a sweeping curve and continues over the viaduct and the wild #Landwassertal to #Thusis. Thank you for the great photo @thomas.luisier! -
